{The bidding has been as shown. The contract is 6NT 

Lead the \D2, or perhaps the \S9. Admittedly the \HQ looks very tempting, but resist the temptation.

Since dummy bid \Hs, don't help declarer by leading the suit. Declarer has 11 tricks, and will hope to pick up one more in \Cs, but that won't happen.

But if you start with the \HQ, he will win with his \HK and can then establish an extra \H winner by leading through your \H J 10 into dummy's \H A 9.

With any lead other than a \H honor he cannot come to 12 tricks.}
[Play "W"]D2

